    <p>Guideline 1.1 talks about non-text contet presented to the user that has text alternatives, except for certain situations, such as controls, time-based mediua, test, seonsory, captcha, and decoration.</p>
    
    <p>Guideline 1.2 talks about different alternatives time-based media is presented. Many of the options are prerecorded, such as captions, sign language, and audio description. There is also live audio.</p>
    
    <p>Guideline 1.3 shows how you can create and present content in different ways without losing out on information or structure. This can be done by structuring based on info and relationships, meaningful sequences, and sensory characteristics. Identifying the purpose of things can also help. </p>

